<subSubSection id="19B374F5180C54075176ADD586C39BF8" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="B8D873CC07CF4E75F915714804469655" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="04C8D3DD839D5F83966FE693C024A313" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The indumentum of 
<taxonomicName id="197B9C73661EBE294A5D2D5BD793CC60" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="D." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. macrosepala" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrosepala">
<emphasis id="44DDEE9A5404902B382F89CB23187BEF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. macrosepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="088D46F25AD493873EC0F55932331860" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="D." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. densiflora" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="densiflora">
<emphasis id="20C0E74651E99CAE13A815BBB6D36278" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. densiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the former species is different in the long, lanceolate calyx lobes. 
<bibRefCitation id="E8DAD3054883895430FB1030E89BD493" author="Maxwell, JF" journalOrPublisher="Gardens' Bulletin (Singapore)" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="312 - 327" refId="B44" refString="Maxwell, JF, 1980b. Taxonomic notes on the tribe Dissochaeteae (Naudin) Triana (Melastomataceae). Gardens' Bulletin (Singapore) 33: 312 - 327" title="Taxonomic notes on the tribe Dissochaeteae (Naudin) Triana (Melastomataceae)." volume="33" year="1980 b">Maxwell (1980b)</bibRefCitation>
considered both species as varieties of 
<taxonomicName id="0BC5B0A39B7624536E17287FB042A7DA" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="D." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. rostrata" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rostrata">
<emphasis id="3AEACE69522D7580CA7341723BB39CA6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. rostrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="9FA5BB83AD5DE58B5C7D342AFF0A8117" author="Stapf, O" editor="Gibbs, LS" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Linnean Society, Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="78 - 81" refId="B71" refString="Stapf, O, Green, ML, 1914. Melastomaceae. In: Gibbs, LS, Ed., A contribution to the flora and plant formations of Mount Kinabalu and the Highlands of British North Borneo. Journal of the Linnean Society, Botany 42: 78 - 81" title="Melastomaceae." volume="42" volumeTitle="A contribution to the flora and plant formations of Mount Kinabalu and the Highlands of British North Borneo." year="1914">Stapf and Green (1914)</bibRefCitation>
incorrectly noted that the species has four stamens, but it has 8 stamens like the other similar species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
